The length of a vector, $\Vert \mathbf{x} \Vert$ where \textbf{x} has
components $[x_1,x_2,x_3]$ is,

\begin{align*}
||\mathbf{x}||=\sqrt{x_1^2+x_2^2+x_3^2}.
\end{align*}

Since \textbf{x}={[}1,-1,-1{]} then

\begin{align*}
||\mathbf{x}||=\sqrt{1+1+1}=\sqrt{3}.
\end{align*}

